rComments: The course was very interesting and I liked the lectures. The professor is very helpful.
This is a C level course, complex obviously, but highly recommended for people interested in grad school in health studies. Great Professor.

The course was definitely a lot harder than I anticipated beforehand. Like someone else said, the instructor wasn't always 100% clear with what he was looking for in terms of the assignments and what would be on the quizzes. Attending class is a must since the readings are of a higher level. Personally, I wouldn't recommend this as an elective.
Prof. was very unclear as far as expectations in the course. Plus the TA was a total ----- when it came to marking.

The topics are really interesting but complex. Some of the readings can be difficult to read so I STRONGLY encourse you to attend lecture. To the other comments, he gives the students a course outline for a reason. Read it and you won't miss anything. The quizzes are pretty easy if you stay on top of your readings.

Really did not like this instructor. Doesn't use a microphone and talks really softly in class so hearing him ain't always easy. Overall, this course would have been much better if he wasn't teaching it. Does not mark fairly and is horrible at keeping the class updated on what's going on in the course. Miss ONE lecture and you will be lost entirely

Did not like this professor very much. Does not take any effort to update the class on what's going on in the course and doesn't make announcements on intranet. So basically if you don't attend class your screwed and will have no clue what's going on.
